# How to Set Up Gmail SMTP Relay on Amazon Linux

Follow these exact steps to configure your Amazon Linux EC2 server to send emails using Gmail SMTP:

## âœ… Step 1: Install Required Packages

```bash
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install -y postfix mailx cyrus-sasl-plain
sudo systemctl enable postfix
sudo systemctl start postfix
```

## âœ… Step 2: Configure Postfix for Gmail SMTP

Edit the postfix configuration file:

```bash
sudo vi /etc/postfix/main.cf
```

Add these exact lines at the end:

```
relayhost = [smtp.gmail.com]:587
smtp_use_tls = yes
smtp_sasl_auth_enable = yes
smtp_sasl_password_maps = hash:/etc/postfix/sasl_passwd
smtp_sasl_security_options = noanonymous
smtp_tls_security_level = encrypt
smtp_tls_CAfile = /etc/ssl/certs/ca-bundle.crt
```

## âœ… Step 3: Generate Gmail App Password

- Enable 2-Step Verification: [https://myaccount.google.com/signinoptions/two-step-verification](https://myaccount.google.com/signinoptions/two-step-verification)
- Generate App Password: [https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords](https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords)
- Copy the 16-character password provided, **remove all spaces**.

## âœ… Step 4: Add Gmail credentials to Postfix

Create and edit the credentials file:

```bash
sudo vi /etc/postfix/sasl_passwd
```

Add exactly (without spaces):

```
[smtp.gmail.com]:587 your_email@gmail.com:yourapppassword
```

Save and close the file.

## âœ… Step 5: Secure credentials and reload Postfix

```bash
sudo chmod 600 /etc/postfix/sasl_passwd
sudo postmap /etc/postfix/sasl_passwd
sudo systemctl restart postfix
```

## âœ… Step 6: Allow SMTP Port in EC2 Security Group

- Open your EC2 instance security group.
- Ensure **port 587 outbound (TCP)** is allowed.

## âœ… Step 7: Test Email from Bash

Send a test email:

```bash
echo "Hello from EC2" | mail -s "SMTP Setup Success" your_email@gmail.com
```

## âœ… Step 8: Verify

- Check your Gmail inbox and spam folders.
- Confirm email delivery success with:

```bash
sudo  cat /var/spool/mail/ec2-user
```

ðŸŽ¯ **That's it! Your EC2 instance can now send emails via Gmail SMTP.**
